ORP effect explains why striae are observed between\nnear-perihelion and ~1 AU from the Sun for comets with perihelia less than 0.6\nAU, and solves longstanding problems with moving enough material into the\ncometary tail to form visible striae. We show that SYORP can form striae that\nmatch those of Comet West, and produce a power-law size frequency distribution\nof their parent chunks with an index of -1.4 (-1.1- 2).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 15 Sep 2015 22:05:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-11-25"}
